  <description type="morphology">Spines: central spine yellowish, becoming ashy gray or reddish brown, 1–3.8 cm, minutely scabrous (use 30× lens). Flowers yellow with red centers, leaving obvious, concave abscission scars after fall of flower or fruit; proximal outer tepals obtuse or with broad ± auriculate distal portions; distal ones minutely fringed, acute; inner tepals oblanceolate; filaments reddish, pale yellow, or whitish, collectively spiraled around style; ovary 8–13 mm diam. Fruits displaced away from stem apex by apical growth subsequent to flowering. 2n = 22.</description>
